$Dean's bunt went over the head of 3B Vergez into shallow LF. Vergez chased the ball, SS Jackson covered 3B, and 2B Critz was covering 1B, leaving 2B unoccupied. So Dean tried for a double. Critz raced him to 2B but LF Koenecke's throw sailed over Critz's head. C Hogan chased down the ball near 1B, leaving home plate open, so Dean tried to score. Hogan's throw landed in the stands, but he wasn't charged an error on the play.1932.EDN.regular.comment.csv"
